parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control or fail to stop, leading to accidents.
The failure of the brake pedal can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.

premature wear of parking brake shoes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, become stuck in gear, or leave the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience.

the vehicle is unable to start or move
the transmission gets stuck in third gear
and the instrument panel stops working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door electrical system can cause the door to malfunction, which can lead to inconvenience or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk violently, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the instrument panel or cluster can cause incorrect or missing information, leading to accidents, misjudging speed, or unawareness of vehicle conditions.
symptoms: Odometer and gear display are incorrect

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transfer case can cause the wheels to lock or "hobble" in low-speed turns, leading to loss of control or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Power Train Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle body and power train can cause the vehicle to jerk violently, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
